    <item>
      <title>Announcing Project Oculus v5.0: The Enterprise Agent Coordination Era</title>
      <link>https://detroitautomationacademy.com/blog/posts/announcing-oculus-v5-enterprise-coordination/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 20:30:00 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>https://detroitautomationacademy.com/blog/posts/announcing-oculus-v5-enterprise-coordination/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;the-evolution-of-command-v50&#34;&gt;The Evolution of Command: v5.0&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Today marks a major architectural milestone for Automated Technologies. We have formally successfully transitioned from &lt;strong&gt;Project Oculus v4.0&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;Oculus v5.0&lt;/strong&gt;, evolving our centralized dashboard from a telemetry-passive HUD into a high-fidelity &lt;strong&gt;Enterprise Agent Coordination Hub&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-63-agent-fleet&#34;&gt;The 63-Agent Fleet&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As our ecosystem expanded across the DAA, AT_Music, AT_Wealth, AT_Diary, and Oculus domains, the need for unified fleet management became critical. Oculus v5.0 now tracks and orchestrates &lt;strong&gt;63 specialized agents&lt;/strong&gt;, incorporating both our core global team and the newly registered domain-specific fleet from the &lt;code&gt;clawd&lt;/code&gt; framework.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>DAA CRM Live: From Zero to Cloud Run in One Session</title>
      <link>https://detroitautomationacademy.com/blog/posts/daa-crm-cloud-run-deployment/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 05:00:00 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>https://detroitautomationacademy.com/blog/posts/daa-crm-cloud-run-deployment/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Tonight we shipped the DAA CRM from a broken build to a fully deployed, publicly accessible system in a single engineering session. Here&amp;rsquo;s what that actually looked like.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;starting-point-five-consecutive-build-failures&#34;&gt;Starting Point: Five Consecutive Build Failures&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;deploy.sh&lt;/code&gt; script existed. The Docker images existed. What didn&amp;rsquo;t exist: a working build.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The first failure was a Go syntax error in &lt;code&gt;backend/main.go&lt;/code&gt; — a raw newline embedded inside a string literal:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;2&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;3&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;4&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;5&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;6&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go&#34; data-lang=&#34;go&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;// Broken&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;fmt&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;Printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;DAA CRM Backend starting on port %s...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;port&lt;/span&gt;)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;// Fixed&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;fmt&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;Printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;DAA CRM Backend starting on port %s...\n&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;port&lt;/span&gt;)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Go doesn&amp;rsquo;t allow unescaped newlines inside string literals. The fix was one character. The lesson: always verify generated code with a local &lt;code&gt;go build&lt;/code&gt; before pushing to Cloud Build.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
